In what circumstances and how do we obtain your consent to install cookies? What are your rights with regard to cookies?
Circumstances for obtaining consent, the scope of your consent, and exceptions
Important: The information below regarding your consent to or refusal of the use of cookies applies independently to our Site and to each of our mobile game applications. Furthermore, your consent or refusal/retraction of consent is obtained independently with regard to the use of cookies on our Site and on each of our game applications.
For example, your consent to the use of one or other cookie(s) on our Site does not constitute consent to the use of the same cookies or similar cookies on all or any of our mobile game applications. Furthermore, your settings for cookies used on our Site are separate from any settings you may opt for on our mobile game applications.
3.1.   The installation of a cookie on a computer or terminal, as well as reading of this cookie via our Site or our mobile game applications, are in principle
subject to the consent of the user
, i.e. to a free, specific, clear and unequivocal demonstration of the user’s will granting their agreement for this purpose, and doing so
separately for each purpose pursued by the cookies concerned
. This consent is obtained via our
cookie management module (accessible from
the footer of every page of our Site by clicking on the Cookie Management Module link or, in the case of our mobile applications, directly in the application)
under the terms and conditions detailed below.
Furthermore, during the user’s first visit to our Site or to one of our mobile game applications, they are asked if they accept the cookies for which consent must be obtained, classed into different categories according to their purpose, before such cookies are installed on their computer or terminal. The cookies that are subject to such consent  are not installed until the user expressly accepts them, either comprehensively by clicking on the Accept All button, which allows you to accept all cookies, or distributively for each purpose by clicking the Accept button, which allows you to accept each of the categories (i.e. by purpose) of the cookies concerned using our cookie management module (i.e. the module provides the user with the opportunity to consent to or refuse the use of cookies depending on their purpose).
Important:
– In cases where your consent is required, such consent is strictly optional, and you can simply refuse to grant it.
In any case, if you give your consent to the installation and reading of all or some of these cookies,
you will of course retain the possibility to retract your consent at any later date using the cookie management module.
– Furthermore, unless you express your will to the contrary using our cookie management module under the terms and conditions detailed below,
your choice (comprehensive
consent, partial consent, or refusal) will be retained for a period of 6 months, at the end of which time you will be asked again for your consent to or refusal of the installation of such cookies.
3.2
Exception to consent for so-called “functional” cookies used by our Site and our mobile game applications.
Such cookies are not subject to your prior consent. Furthermore, these cookies are installed automatically when you browse our Site or use our mobile game applications, without your prior consent being obtained. Insofar as these cookies are necessary to offer you a better user experience or to allow you to benefit from certain functions of our Site and/or our mobile applications, we do not offer you any dedicated technical means to refuse the installation of these cookies or to disable them. However, you have the option of (as you do with certain other cookies) disabling them by other means, for example by using the functions offered by your browser or terminal, while bearing in mind that in this case you risk not being able to access our Site or our mobile game applications, and/or not receiving correctly the content and information available on, and/or not being able to benefit from all the functionality of our Site or our mobile game applications.
The practical methods of obtaining your choices with regard to cookies (consent/refusal)
The cookie management module holds information for the user about the cookies that may be installed/read in their terminal as a result of browsing our Site and/or using our mobile game applications (see also the details of these cookies in Article 3 hereof). It displays on our Site and on our mobile game applications during the user’s first visit and then, regardless of the user’s choice (comprehensive consent, partial consent, or refusal), displays again every 6 months. It will also display again if the user deletes their cookies using the functions of their browser or their terminal.
The module offers the user several choices:
either to consent comprehensively to the use of all the cookies by clicking on Accept All: all the cookies will then be installed,
or to refuse comprehensively the use of all the cookies by clicking on Refuse All: only “functional” cookies will then be installed,
or to personalize their choice by managing in a more careful way the cookies they accept (or refuse). In this case, the user is asked to click on the Authorize or Refuse buttons for each category of cookies concerned in our cookie management module, and in order to personalize their choices (on the understanding that, in the case of “functional” cookies that are not subject to prior consent, such cookies will be installed by default and cannot be refused by the user via our cookie management module), the user will then have to register their choices by clicking on Validate My Choices. It is accepted as a principle that if the user has not clicked Authorize for a cookie (regardless of whether or not they have clicked Refuse for that cookie), the cookie will be regarded as refused and not installed. This page also offers the user to Accept All or Refuse All.
The user can also configure their choices with regard to the companies (third parties) using cookies on the Site and/or on our mobile game applications and the destination companies of the data collected through such cookies by specifying if they want to identify such companies as Authorized or Blocked, it being understood that:
in principle, when a user consents to a category/a purpose of cookies, then all the partners using those cookies and/or all the companies that may be destinations of the data collected in this way are automatically considered Authorized (but only for the purposes of cookies authorized by the user);
the user has the ability to refuse some of the partners using these cookies and/or all the companies that may be destinations for the data collected in this way by clicking, on the appropriate page of the cookie management module accessed via a button, on the Block button corresponding to the partners or destination companies that they want to refuse.
To access our cookie management module, click on the Cookie Management Module link that can be found in the footer of all the pages of our Site. In the case of our mobile game applications, the location of the module depends on the application.
In any case, all consent on your part to the use of cookies can be freely retracted at any time by deactivating one or more of the cookies in the manner described below.
The practical methods of modifying your choices with regard to cookies (retracting your consent or refusal)
You have available to you at all times several options for modifying the choices that you have made regarding cookies, in particular, retract your consent to or refuse their use (i.e. the installation/reading of cookies in your terminal).
3.3     You can at any time, simply and free of charge, on a distributive basis according to the purposes pursued by such cookies, choose to retract your consent to or refuse the use of cookies other than “functional” cookies on your computer or terminal using the cookie management module.
To do this, simply click on the Cookie Management Module link that can be found in the footer of all the pages of our Site. In the case of our mobile game applications, the location of the module depends on the application. Then:
click on the Refuse button corresponding to the cookies you want to uninstall,
register your choices by clicking on Validate My Choices.
Or:
click on the Refuse All button.
The user has the ability to configure their choices with regard to the partner companies using these cookies and the destinations for the data collected through such cookies by clicking, on the appropriate page of the cookie management module accessed as described above, the Block button corresponding to the partners or destination companies that they want to refuse.
3.4     You can also, if you prefer, have recourse to one of the options below.
Your browser settings (with regard to the cookies that may be used on our Site)
While most browsers are configured by default and accept the installation of cookies, the user has the possibility, if they wish to, of choosing in their browser settings to accept all cookies or to reject them systematically, or also to choose those cookies that they accept according to the issuer (on the condition that such a function is offered by their browser). Furthermore, the user can regularly delete the cookies on their terminal using their browser.
In any case, these operations must be performed for each terminal: tablets, smartphones, computers, etc.
You can thus freely configure your browser (Internet Explorer, Firefox, Google Chrome, etc.) in such a way that cookies will be:
accepted and installed on your computer or terminal: in this case, the cookies integrated into the pages and content that you view will be systematically installed,
refused: in this case, the cookies integrated into the pages and content that you view will not be installed,
subject every time to your choice: in this case, the installation of cookies will each time be subject to your acceptance or refusal.
To configure your choices for acceptance or refusal of cookies, you will have to take into account the configuration of each browser, as they are all different and change regularly. You will therefore need to refer to the help menu of your browser, which will allow you to find out how to change your cookie preferences. Examples:
For more information about Google Chrome:
https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647?hl=fr&hlrm=en
;
For more information about Firefox:
https://support.mozilla.org/fr/kb/autoriser-bloquer-cookies-preferences-sites?redirectlocale=fr&redirectslug=activer-desactiver-cookies-preferences
and
https://support.mozilla.org/fr/kb/desactiver-cookies-tiers
;
For more information about Internet Explorer:
https://support.microsoft.com/fr-fr/help/17442/windows-internet-explorer-delete-manage-cookies
;
For more information about Safari:
https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/fr-ww/cookies/
and
https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/fr-ww/
;
For more information about Edge:
https://support.microsoft.com/fr-fr/help/4468242/microsoft-edge-browsing-data-and-privacy-microsoft-privacy
;
For more information about Opera™:
https://help.opera.com/en/latest/security-and-privacy/
and
https://help.opera.com/en/latest/web-preferences/#cookies
.
Finally, it should be noted that in their current iterations, browsers:
do not all allow you to sort cookies by their purpose (which means that you are often constrained to choosing between Accept All and Refuse All) ;
do not all allow the user to give a valid expression of consent (which means that, despite the fact that you possibly have given consent to cookies via your browser, we will ask again for your specific consent under the conditions and in the manners cited above before any installation/reading by us of cookies that are subject to your consent);
do not all allow you to express a choice on technologies other than “cookies for tracking browsing” in the strictly limited sense of the term. Furthermore, it is possible that certain cookies, trackers, or other similar technologies are in principle not blocked (e.g.
device fingerprinting
) and can be installed and/or activated despite the fact that you have expressed your refusal via the settings of your browser.
As a result, it is recommended that you use our cookie management module (see above) to manage your choices with regard to cookies on our Site.
Configuration via professional digital advertising platforms
Several professional advertising platforms also offer users the opportunity to define their preferences with regard to targeted/behavioral advertising operated by member companies. In general, these centralized mechanisms do not block the display of all advertisements but prevent targeted/behavioral advertising adapted to the interests of the user, which are defined through their activity on the internet and their browsing history.
For example, the website youronlinechoices.com lists a large number of companies that work with websites to collect and use the information necessary for targeted/behavioral advertising. This website is offered by digital advertising professionals grouped together in the EDAA (European Digital Advertising Alliance) and managed in France by the Interactive Advertising Bureau France. This European platform is shared by hundreds of online advertising professionals and constitutes a centralized interface that allows the user to find out which companies are registered on the platform and offer the option of refusing or accepting the display of targeted/behavioral advertising on the user’s terminal with regard to their browsing information:
http://www.youronlinechoices.com/fr/controler-ses-cookies
.
You can thus control and define your preferences with regard to targeted/behavioral advertising on this website by selecting or deselecting all companies, or by defining your preferences company by company, bearing in mind that you will have to follow the same process on each different browser that you may use.
For another example, a similar platform published by the NAI (Network Advertising Initiative) is available on the page
https://optout.networkadvertising.org/?c=1
and also offers the same functions.
Although these platforms can allow you to manage your preferences regarding targeted advertising, they do not necessarily block advertising in general nor the installation of all cookies.
As a result, it is recommended that you use our cookie management module (see above) to manage your choices with regard to cookies.
Use of third-party tools available online
Certain publishers of the cookies that we use on our Site and on our mobile game applications offer dedicated deactivation modules. It is thus recommended that users familiarize themselves with the information pages listed in the table above (
see the details of the cookies we use in Paragraph 3
) in order to identify these modules if required.
For example, users can familiarize themselves with specific information regarding the Google Analytics deactivation module on the page:
https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/181881?hl=fr&ref_topic=2919631
. The user can also choose to deactivate all Google Analytics cookies directly by visiting the following page:
https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout
.
3.5     You can obtain information on how to control your data while browsing the internet on the website of the French agency on data protection, the Commission Nationale de l’Informatique et des Libertés or CNIL (
https://www.cnil.fr/fr/maitriser-mes-donnees
, particularly
https://www.cnil.fr/fr/cookies-les-outils-pour-les-maitriser
). In this regard, third-party cookies are not normally necessary for you to enjoy the resources available on the internet. If you wish to limit your digital footprint, you are advised to refuse them by default, as recommended by CNIL.
How does TAPNATION process your personal data?
Cookies do not in and of themselves constitute personal data. However, they may effect the collection of information that can be qualified as personal data and therefore lead to the processing of such data.
In this regard, you are hereby informed that, by consenting to the installation of all or part of the cookies, you consent to the processing of your personal data collected in this way for the relevant purposes, it being understood that this processing may involve the processing, combining and cross-referencing of a significant volume of such data about you from various sources.
Subscriptions
Subscription-based billing is applied to some parts of the Service. Subscription provides access to dynamic content or services from within the Game on an ongoing basis.
Subscriptions may be available at different fees chargeable for a set period of time specified in the Game (“Subscription Period”). Payment will be taken from Your iTunes or Google Play account (“Account”) when You confirm the Subscription by available confirmation tools of the Game.
Trial Subscription is offered free of charge for certain period of time from activation specified in the relevant offer in the Game. If You do not cancel the Subscription within such period, Subscription Fee shall be taken from Your Account when the trial period expires. Please note that Your Subscription begins immediately after the activation of a trial Subscription, not after the seven-days trial period. You may cancel a subscription during its free trial period using the Subscription setting of Your Account. Tap Nation can not cancel your free-trial subscription if it has already been activated.
Subscription is automatically renewable, unless You turn off it at least 24 hours before the expiry of the current Subscription. Subscription Fee shall be taken from Your Account during 24 hours preceding the expiry of the current Subscription. In case Subscription Fee cannot be taken from Your Account due to absence of monetary funds, invalidity of credit card or for any other reasons, Your Subscription is automatically canceled.
Once You have bought a Subscription, You can manage it and switch off automatic renewal at any time after the purchase in Your Account setting. You cannot cancel Your current Subscription if it has already been activated.
Except when required by law, paid Subscription Fees are non-refundable.
Tap Nation in its sole discretion and at any time may modify the Subscription Fee. Any Subscription Fee change will become effective at the end of the current Subscription period. You will be provided a reasonable prior notice of any change in Subscription Fee. If You do not take action to agree to the increase in Subscription Fee, Your Subscription shall expire at the end of the current Subscription period.
For all information regarding the processing of your personal data by TAPNATION, particularly the processing of personal data obtained via the cookies integrated into our Site and/or our mobile game applications, we ask you to consult our
Data Protection Policy
.
